Encode ’Genre" with one hot encoding method


data1=data%>%select(id, genre_1, genre_2, genre_3)
genre = gather(data1,colname, genre, genre_1:genre_3)
genre %>%arrange(id)    

library(caret)     
dummy = dummyVars('~genre', data=genre)
dum = data.frame(predict(dummy, newdata = genre))
dum

enc= cbind(genre[('id')],dum)
enc = enc %>%mutate_all(~replace(.,is.na(.),0))%>%arrange(id)    
genre_enc = enc%>% group_by(id)%>%summarize(across(everything(),list(max)))    
genre_enc

merge data1(genre encode) with data

data2 <- merge(data,genre_enc,by="id", all.x = T)
data2

summary of characters, words, sentences

df_overview %>%
  select(overview)%>%
  mutate(characters = nchar(overview),
         words = str_count(overview,pattern='\\S+'),
         sentences = str_count(overview,pattern="[A-Za-z,;'\"\\s]+[^.!?]*[.?!]"))%>%
  summarize_at(c('characters','words','sentences'),.funs = mean,na.rm=T)

corelation btwn length and rating

r_characters = cor.test(nchar(df_overview$overview),df_overview$weighted_rating)

r_words = cor.test(str_count(string = df_overview$overview,pattern = '\\S+'),
                   df_overview$weighted_rating)

r_sentences = cor.test(str_count(string = df_overview$overview,pattern = "[A-Za-z,;'\"\\s]+[^.!?]*[.?!]"),
                       df_overview$weighted_rating)

correlations = data.frame(r = c(r_characters$estimate, r_words$estimate, r_sentences$estimate),
                          p_value=c(r_characters$p.value, r_words$p.value, r_sentences$p.value))

rownames(correlations) = c('Characters','Words','Sentences')
correlations

Joining, by = "word"

proportion of positive and negative words

df_overview %>%
  select(overview)%>%
  unnest_tokens(output=word,input=overview)%>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments('bing'))%>%
  group_by(sentiment)%>%
  summarize(n = n())%>%
  mutate(proportion = n/sum(n))%>% 
  ungroup()
Joining, by = "word"

correlation between Positive Words and Review Rating (PS ###look at code in html to double check)

df_overview%>%
  unnest_tokens(output = word, input = overview)%>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments('bing'))%>%
  group_by(weighted_rating)%>%
  summarize(positive_words = sum(sentiment=='positive'),
            negative_words = sum(sentiment=='negative'),
            proportion_positive = positive_words/(positive_words+negative_words))%>%
  ungroup()%>%
  summarize(correlation = cor(proportion_positive,weighted_rating))
